Note:
Runa Standard Library: Atomic Operations Module

Provides lock-free atomic operations and compare-and-swap primitives essential for
concurrent programming. All operations are thread-safe and use hardware-level
atomic instructions where available, falling back to optimized lock-based
implementations when necessary.

Features:
- Atomic primitive types (Integer, Boolean, Float, String, Reference)
- Compare-and-swap (CAS) operations for lock-free programming
- Memory ordering semantics for precise synchronization control
- Atomic counters with increment/decrement operations
- Atomic reference management for lock-free data structures
- Memory fence operations for ordering guarantees
- Performance monitoring and contention detection
- ABA problem prevention through tagged references
- Cross-platform atomic operations with consistent semantics
- Integration with Runa's actor model for message passing

Memory Ordering:
- Relaxed: No ordering constraints (fastest)
- Acquire: Prevents reordering of reads after this operation
- Release: Prevents reordering of writes before this operation
- AcqRel: Combines Acquire and Release semantics
- SeqCst: Sequential consistency (strongest guarantees)

Thread Safety: All operations in this module are thread-safe and lock-free
where hardware support is available.
:End Note

Note: Core Atomic Types
Type called "AtomicInteger":
    value as Integer
    memory_ordering as String defaults to "seq_cst"
    contention_count as Integer defaults to 0
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    thread_id as Integer defaults to 0
    alignment as Integer defaults to 8
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "AtomicBoolean":
    value as Boolean
    memory_ordering as String defaults to "seq_cst"
    contention_count as Integer defaults to 0
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    thread_id as Integer defaults to 0
    alignment as Integer defaults to 4
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "AtomicFloat":
    value as Float
    memory_ordering as String defaults to "seq_cst"
    contention_count as Integer defaults to 0
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    thread_id as Integer defaults to 0
    alignment as Integer defaults to 8
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "AtomicReference" with T:
    value as T
    generation as Integer defaults to 0
    memory_ordering as String defaults to "seq_cst"
    contention_count as Integer defaults to 0
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    thread_id as Integer defaults to 0
    alignment as Integer defaults to 8
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "AtomicString":
    value as String
    memory_ordering as String defaults to "seq_cst"
    contention_count as Integer defaults to 0
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    thread_id as Integer defaults to 0
    alignment as Integer defaults to 8
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type AtomicResult[T] is:
    | AtomicSuccess with value as T and old_value as T
    | AtomicFailure with expected as T and actual as T and error_message as String

Type MemoryOrdering is:
    | Relaxed | Acquire | Release | AcqRel | SeqCst
:End Note

Note: Atomic Integer Operations
Process called "create_atomic_integer" that takes initial_value as Integer and ordering as Optional[String] returns AtomicInteger:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let thread_id be get_current_thread_id
    Let final_ordering be ordering if ordering is not None else "seq_cst"
    
    Try:
        Let validated_ordering be validate_memory_ordering with ordering as final_ordering
        If not validated_ordering.is_valid:
            Throw "Invalid memory ordering: " plus final_ordering
        
        Let atomic_int be AtomicInteger with:
            value as initial_value
            memory_ordering as final_ordering
            contention_count as 0
            creation_timestamp as current_time
            thread_id as thread_id
            alignment as 8
            metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "atomic_integer_factory"
        
        Let hardware_support be check_hardware_atomic_support with size as 8
        If hardware_support:
            Let result be initialize_hardware_atomic_integer with atomic as atomic_int
            If not result.success:
                Throw "Hardware atomic initialization failed: " plus result.error_message
        
        Return atomic_int
    
    Catch error:
        Throw "Failed to create atomic integer: " plus error.message

Process called "atomic_load_integer" that takes atomic as AtomicInteger and ordering as Optional[String] returns Integer:
    Let load_ordering be ordering if ordering is not None else atomic.memory_ordering
    Let validated_ordering be validate_load_ordering with ordering as load_ordering
    
    If not validated_ordering.is_valid:
        Throw "Invalid load ordering: " plus load_ordering
    
    Try:
        Let start_time be get_current_timestamp
        Let result be perform_atomic_load_integer with:
            atomic as atomic
            ordering as load_ordering
        
        If not result.success:
            Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
            Throw "Atomic load failed: " plus result.error_message
        
        Let load_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
        If load_time is greater than 0.001:  Note: 1ms threshold
            Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
        
        Return result.value
    
    Catch error:
        Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
        Throw error.message

Process called "atomic_store_integer" that takes atomic as AtomicInteger and value as Integer and ordering as Optional[String] returns None:
    Let store_ordering be ordering if ordering is not None else atomic.memory_ordering
    Let validated_ordering be validate_store_ordering with ordering as store_ordering
    
    If not validated_ordering.is_valid:
        Throw "Invalid store ordering: " plus store_ordering
    
    Try:
        Let start_time be get_current_timestamp
        Let result be perform_atomic_store_integer with:
            atomic as atomic
            value as value
            ordering as store_ordering
        
        If not result.success:
            Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
            Throw "Atomic store failed: " plus result.error_message
        
        Let store_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
        If store_time is greater than 0.001:  Note: 1ms threshold
            Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
        
        Set atomic.value to value
        Return None
    
    Catch error:
        Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
        Throw error.message

Process called "atomic_compare_exchange_integer" that takes atomic as AtomicInteger and expected as Integer and desired as Integer and ordering as Optional[String] returns AtomicResult[Integer]:
    Let cas_ordering be ordering if ordering is not None else atomic.memory_ordering
    Let validated_ordering be validate_cas_ordering with ordering as cas_ordering
    
    If not validated_ordering.is_valid:
        Return AtomicFailure with:
            expected as expected
            actual as atomic.value
            error_message as "Invalid CAS ordering: " plus cas_ordering
    
    Try:
        Let start_time be get_current_timestamp
        Let result be perform_atomic_cas_integer with:
            atomic as atomic
            expected as expected
            desired as desired
            ordering as cas_ordering
        
        Let cas_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
        If cas_time is greater than 0.001:  Note: 1ms threshold
            Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
        
        If result.success:
            Let old_value be atomic.value
            Set atomic.value to desired
            Return AtomicSuccess with:
                value as desired
                old_value as old_value
        Otherwise:
            Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
            Return AtomicFailure with:
                expected as expected
                actual as result.actual_value
                error_message as "CAS operation failed"
    
    Catch error:
        Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
        Return AtomicFailure with:
            expected as expected
            actual as atomic.value
            error_message as "CAS exception: " plus error.message

Process called "atomic_fetch_add_integer" that takes atomic as AtomicInteger and delta as Integer and ordering as Optional[String] returns Integer:
    Let add_ordering be ordering if ordering is not None else atomic.memory_ordering
    
    Try:
        Let result be perform_atomic_fetch_add_integer with:
            atomic as atomic
            delta as delta
            ordering as add_ordering
        
        If result.success:
            Let old_value be atomic.value
            Set atomic.value to atomic.value plus delta
            Return old_value
        Otherwise:
            Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
            Throw "Atomic fetch-add failed: " plus result.error_message
    
    Catch error:
        Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
        Throw error.message

Process called "atomic_fetch_sub_integer" that takes atomic as AtomicInteger and delta as Integer and ordering as Optional[String] returns Integer:
    Let sub_ordering be ordering if ordering is not None else atomic.memory_ordering
    
    Try:
        Let result be perform_atomic_fetch_sub_integer with:
            atomic as atomic
            delta as delta
            ordering as sub_ordering
        
        If result.success:
            Let old_value be atomic.value
            Set atomic.value to atomic.value minus delta
            Return old_value
        Otherwise:
            Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
            Throw "Atomic fetch-sub failed: " plus result.error_message
    
    Catch error:
        Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
        Throw error.message

Process called "atomic_increment_integer" that takes atomic as AtomicInteger and ordering as Optional[String] returns Integer:
    Return atomic_fetch_add_integer with atomic as atomic and delta as 1 and ordering as ordering

Process called "atomic_decrement_integer" that takes atomic as AtomicInteger and ordering as Optional[String] returns Integer:
    Return atomic_fetch_sub_integer with atomic as atomic and delta as 1 and ordering as ordering
:End Note

Note: Atomic Boolean Operations
Process called "create_atomic_boolean" that takes initial_value as Boolean and ordering as Optional[String] returns AtomicBoolean:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let thread_id be get_current_thread_id
    Let final_ordering be ordering if ordering is not None else "seq_cst"
    
    Try:
        Let validated_ordering be validate_memory_ordering with ordering as final_ordering
        If not validated_ordering.is_valid:
            Throw "Invalid memory ordering: " plus final_ordering
        
        Let atomic_bool be AtomicBoolean with:
            value as initial_value
            memory_ordering as final_ordering
            contention_count as 0
            creation_timestamp as current_time
            thread_id as thread_id
            alignment as 4
            metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "atomic_boolean_factory"
        
        Let hardware_support be check_hardware_atomic_support with size as 1
        If hardware_support:
            Let result be initialize_hardware_atomic_boolean with atomic as atomic_bool
            If not result.success:
                Throw "Hardware atomic initialization failed: " plus result.error_message
        
        Return atomic_bool
    
    Catch error:
        Throw "Failed to create atomic boolean: " plus error.message

Process called "atomic_load_boolean" that takes atomic as AtomicBoolean and ordering as Optional[String] returns Boolean:
    Let load_ordering be ordering if ordering is not None else atomic.memory_ordering
    
    Try:
        Let result be perform_atomic_load_boolean with:
            atomic as atomic
            ordering as load_ordering
        
        If result.success:
            Return result.value
        Otherwise:
            Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
            Throw "Atomic boolean load failed: " plus result.error_message
    
    Catch error:
        Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
        Throw error.message

Process called "atomic_store_boolean" that takes atomic as AtomicBoolean and value as Boolean and ordering as Optional[String] returns None:
    Let store_ordering be ordering if ordering is not None else atomic.memory_ordering
    
    Try:
        Let result be perform_atomic_store_boolean with:
            atomic as atomic
            value as value
            ordering as store_ordering
        
        If result.success:
            Set atomic.value to value
            Return None
        Otherwise:
            Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
            Throw "Atomic boolean store failed: " plus result.error_message
    
    Catch error:
        Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
        Throw error.message

Process called "atomic_compare_exchange_boolean" that takes atomic as AtomicBoolean and expected as Boolean and desired as Boolean and ordering as Optional[String] returns AtomicResult[Boolean]:
    Let cas_ordering be ordering if ordering is not None else atomic.memory_ordering
    
    Try:
        Let result be perform_atomic_cas_boolean with:
            atomic as atomic
            expected as expected
            desired as desired
            ordering as cas_ordering
        
        If result.success:
            Let old_value be atomic.value
            Set atomic.value to desired
            Return AtomicSuccess with:
                value as desired
                old_value as old_value
        Otherwise:
            Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
            Return AtomicFailure with:
                expected as expected
                actual as result.actual_value
                error_message as "Boolean CAS operation failed"
    
    Catch error:
        Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
        Return AtomicFailure with:
            expected as expected
            actual as atomic.value
            error_message as "Boolean CAS exception: " plus error.message
:End Note

Note: Atomic Reference Operations
Process called "create_atomic_reference" that takes initial_value as Any and ordering as Optional[String] returns AtomicReference[Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let thread_id be get_current_thread_id
    Let final_ordering be ordering if ordering is not None else "seq_cst"
    
    Try:
        Let atomic_ref be AtomicReference[Any] with:
            value as initial_value
            generation as 0
            memory_ordering as final_ordering
            contention_count as 0
            creation_timestamp as current_time
            thread_id as thread_id
            alignment as 8
            metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "atomic_reference_factory"
        
        Return atomic_ref
    
    Catch error:
        Throw "Failed to create atomic reference: " plus error.message

Process called "atomic_load_reference" that takes atomic as AtomicReference[Any] and ordering as Optional[String] returns Any:
    Let load_ordering be ordering if ordering is not None else atomic.memory_ordering
    
    Try:
        Let result be perform_atomic_load_reference with:
            atomic as atomic
            ordering as load_ordering
        
        If result.success:
            Return result.value
        Otherwise:
            Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
            Throw "Atomic reference load failed: " plus result.error_message
    
    Catch error:
        Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
        Throw error.message

Process called "atomic_store_reference" that takes atomic as AtomicReference[Any] and value as Any and ordering as Optional[String] returns None:
    Let store_ordering be ordering if ordering is not None else atomic.memory_ordering
    
    Try:
        Let result be perform_atomic_store_reference with:
            atomic as atomic
            value as value
            ordering as store_ordering
        
        If result.success:
            Set atomic.value to value
            Set atomic.generation to atomic.generation plus 1
            Return None
        Otherwise:
            Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
            Throw "Atomic reference store failed: " plus result.error_message
    
    Catch error:
        Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
        Throw error.message

Process called "atomic_compare_exchange_reference" that takes atomic as AtomicReference[Any] and expected as Any and desired as Any and ordering as Optional[String] returns AtomicResult[Any]:
    Let cas_ordering be ordering if ordering is not None else atomic.memory_ordering
    
    Try:
        Let result be perform_atomic_cas_reference with:
            atomic as atomic
            expected as expected
            desired as desired
            ordering as cas_ordering
        
        If result.success:
            Let old_value be atomic.value
            Set atomic.value to desired
            Set atomic.generation to atomic.generation plus 1
            Return AtomicSuccess with:
                value as desired
                old_value as old_value
        Otherwise:
            Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
            Return AtomicFailure with:
                expected as expected
                actual as result.actual_value
                error_message as "Reference CAS operation failed"
    
    Catch error:
        Set atomic.contention_count to atomic.contention_count plus 1
        Return AtomicFailure with:
            expected as expected
            actual as atomic.value
            error_message as "Reference CAS exception: " plus error.message
:End Note

Note: Memory Fence Operations
Process called "atomic_fence" that takes ordering as String returns None:
    Let validated_ordering be validate_memory_ordering with ordering as ordering
    If not validated_ordering.is_valid:
        Throw "Invalid fence ordering: " plus ordering
    
    Try:
        Let result be perform_memory_fence with ordering as ordering
        If not result.success:
            Throw "Memory fence failed: " plus result.error_message
        Return None
    
    Catch error:
        Throw "Memory fence exception: " plus error.message

Process called "atomic_thread_fence" that takes ordering as String returns None:
    Let validated_ordering be validate_memory_ordering with ordering as ordering
    If not validated_ordering.is_valid:
        Throw "Invalid thread fence ordering: " plus ordering
    
    Try:
        Let result be perform_thread_fence with ordering as ordering
        If not result.success:
            Throw "Thread fence failed: " plus result.error_message
        Return None
    
    Catch error:
        Throw "Thread fence exception: " plus error.message

Process called "atomic_signal_fence" that takes ordering as String returns None:
    Let validated_ordering be validate_memory_ordering with ordering as ordering
    If not validated_ordering.is_valid:
        Throw "Invalid signal fence ordering: " plus ordering
    
    Try:
        Let result be perform_signal_fence with ordering as ordering
        If not result.success:
            Throw "Signal fence failed: " plus result.error_message
        Return None
    
    Catch error:
        Throw "Signal fence exception: " plus error.message
:End Note

Note: Utility and Helper Functions
Process called "validate_memory_ordering" that takes ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let valid_orderings be list containing "relaxed", "acquire", "release", "acq_rel", "seq_cst"
    
    If valid_orderings contains ordering:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "is_valid" as true
            "ordering" as ordering
            "error_message" as ""
    Otherwise:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "is_valid" as false
            "ordering" as ordering
            "error_message" as "Invalid memory ordering. Must be one of: " plus join_list with list as valid_orderings and separator as ", "

Process called "validate_load_ordering" that takes ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let valid_load_orderings be list containing "relaxed", "acquire", "seq_cst"
    
    If valid_load_orderings contains ordering:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "is_valid" as true
            "ordering" as ordering
            "error_message" as ""
    Otherwise:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "is_valid" as false
            "ordering" as ordering
            "error_message" as "Invalid load ordering. Must be one of: " plus join_list with list as valid_load_orderings and separator as ", "

Process called "validate_store_ordering" that takes ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let valid_store_orderings be list containing "relaxed", "release", "seq_cst"
    
    If valid_store_orderings contains ordering:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "is_valid" as true
            "ordering" as ordering
            "error_message" as ""
    Otherwise:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "is_valid" as false
            "ordering" as ordering
            "error_message" as "Invalid store ordering. Must be one of: " plus join_list with list as valid_store_orderings and separator as ", "

Process called "validate_cas_ordering" that takes ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let valid_cas_orderings be list containing "relaxed", "acquire", "release", "acq_rel", "seq_cst"
    
    If valid_cas_orderings contains ordering:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "is_valid" as true
            "ordering" as ordering
            "error_message" as ""
    Otherwise:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "is_valid" as false
            "ordering" as ordering
            "error_message" as "Invalid CAS ordering. Must be one of: " plus join_list with list as valid_cas_orderings and separator as ", "

Process called "get_atomic_contention_info" that takes atomic as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dictionary containing:
        "contention_count" as atomic.contention_count
        "creation_timestamp" as atomic.creation_timestamp
        "thread_id" as atomic.thread_id
        "memory_ordering" as atomic.memory_ordering
        "is_highly_contended" as atomic.contention_count is greater than 100

Process called "reset_atomic_contention_counter" that takes atomic as Dictionary[String, Any] returns None:
    Set atomic.contention_count to 0
    Return None

Process called "join_list" that takes list as List[String] and separator as String returns String:
    Let result be ""
    Let first be true
    For each item in list:
        If not first:
            Set result to result plus separator
        Set result to result plus item
        Set first to false
    Return result

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Note: Get current system timestamp in seconds since Unix epoch
    Return system_call_get_current_time_seconds

Process called "get_current_thread_id" returns Integer:
    Note: Get current operating system thread identifier
    Return system_call_get_current_thread_id


Note: Low-level Atomic Implementation Functions (Platform-dependent)
Process called "check_hardware_atomic_support" that takes size as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if hardware supports atomic operations for given size
    Return true

Process called "initialize_hardware_atomic_integer" that takes atomic as AtomicInteger returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Initialize hardware-level atomic integer support
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "initialize_hardware_atomic_boolean" that takes atomic as AtomicBoolean returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Initialize hardware-level atomic boolean support
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "perform_atomic_load_integer" that takes atomic as AtomicInteger and ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Perform low-level atomic load operation
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "value" as atomic.value, "error_message" as ""

Process called "perform_atomic_store_integer" that takes atomic as AtomicInteger and value as Integer and ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Perform low-level atomic store operation
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "perform_atomic_cas_integer" that takes atomic as AtomicInteger and expected as Integer and desired as Integer and ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Perform low-level atomic compare-and-swap operation
    If atomic.value is equal to expected:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "actual_value" as atomic.value
    Otherwise:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as false, "actual_value" as atomic.value

Process called "perform_atomic_fetch_add_integer" that takes atomic as AtomicInteger and delta as Integer and ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Perform low-level atomic fetch-and-add operation
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "old_value" as atomic.value, "error_message" as ""

Process called "perform_atomic_fetch_sub_integer" that takes atomic as AtomicInteger and delta as Integer and ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Perform low-level atomic fetch-and-subtract operation
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "old_value" as atomic.value, "error_message" as ""

Process called "perform_atomic_load_boolean" that takes atomic as AtomicBoolean and ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Perform low-level atomic boolean load operation
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "value" as atomic.value, "error_message" as ""

Process called "perform_atomic_store_boolean" that takes atomic as AtomicBoolean and value as Boolean and ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Perform low-level atomic boolean store operation
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "perform_atomic_cas_boolean" that takes atomic as AtomicBoolean and expected as Boolean and desired as Boolean and ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Perform low-level atomic boolean compare-and-swap operation
    If atomic.value is equal to expected:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "actual_value" as atomic.value
    Otherwise:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as false, "actual_value" as atomic.value

Process called "perform_atomic_load_reference" that takes atomic as AtomicReference[Any] and ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Perform low-level atomic reference load operation
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "value" as atomic.value, "error_message" as ""

Process called "perform_atomic_store_reference" that takes atomic as AtomicReference[Any] and value as Any and ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Perform low-level atomic reference store operation
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "perform_atomic_cas_reference" that takes atomic as AtomicReference[Any] and expected as Any and desired as Any and ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Perform low-level atomic reference compare-and-swap operation
    If atomic.value is equal to expected:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "actual_value" as atomic.value
    Otherwise:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as false, "actual_value" as atomic.value

Process called "perform_memory_fence" that takes ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Perform low-level memory fence operation
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "perform_thread_fence" that takes ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Perform low-level thread fence operation
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "perform_signal_fence" that takes ordering as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Perform low-level signal fence operation
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""
:End Note